text: Mouin AlKazmi () is an Iraqi politician, Leading member of Badr Organization. He is a participant in the upcoming Iraqi elections for the Fatah Alliance. He is member of Baghdad Provincial Council. ==Biography== AlKazmi, (Born in 1975, Baghdad Iraq) is an Iraqi politician and Assistant to the Deputy Chairman of the Popular Mobilization Forces for Combatant Affairs, Chairman of the Committee to Commemorate the Tikrit Massacre.He entered the Iraqi elections as a candidate for the Fatah Alliance. ==References== ==External links== * An Interview with Mouin AlKazmi on Alghad * An Interview with Mouin AlKazmi on Al Rasheed TV Category:Badr Brigade members Category:Iraqi politicians Category:Iraqi soldiers Category:Living people Category:1975 births Category:People from Baghdad Category:Iraqi Shia Muslims
